<DOC><DOCNO> AP891215-0206 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-15-89 2215EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-BRF--RobberSanta     12-15 0159</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Robber Santa,0163</SECOND><HEAD>Singing Santa Robs Bank</HEAD><HEAD>LaserPhoto PX2</HEAD><DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A man wearing a Santa Claus disguise walkedinto a suburban bank, gave the teller a note demanding money andsang softly, ``We wish you a merry Christmas, we wish you a merryChristmas,'' while he waited.   The teller gave him more than $1,000, which bank spokesman PaulLevine called ``just a modest amount.''   ``The guy spent about 30 minutes in the bank, and he stood inline until he got to the teller, showed the note and then softlysang his song,'' FBI spokesman John Kundts said. The FBI did notsay whether he was armed.   The holdup occurred Dec. 4 in a busy branch of Fidelity Bank insuburban West Chester. The FBI announced the robbery Friday inhopes of obtaining information from the public to help solve thecrime.   A bank surveillance picture showed the costumed Santa wearingsunglasses and clutching a pocketbook.</TEXT></DOC>